    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA model ensemble meets acceptance criteria for all three QoIs (E/uval < 1.96). Ten of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors are assessed; one factor (Test conditions) achieves level 2 against a required level 3, which is a documented gap. Two factors (Relevance of QoIs; Relevance of validation activities to COU) were deemed beyond scope and are not assessed. The team judged these omissions acceptable given that ASTM F1717 compliance is a well-established regulatory pathway, and the overall evidence package supports a Medium assurance level for the non-cannulated design. The submission is accepted with the recommendation that the two unassessed factors be formally evaluated in the next revision.",
